			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">Water-Based Paint</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">涂料（水性）</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Emulsion Water-Based Paint; Waterborne Paint,涂料（水性）</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification>
					<common:category level="0">Systems</common:category>
					<common:category level="1">Paints and chemical preparations</common:category>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<sumFormula>Not Available</sumFormula>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Water-based paint is made of microscopic plastic particles of pigment, binders, and water. It is water-soluble but becomes resistant to water when dry. It uses various types of binders like acrylic and alkyd. Water-based paints emit almost 90 percent less VOCs compared to solvent. They are popular for home applications due to their eco-friendliness, odorlessness, and wide range of color options. They do not emit fumes and do not require mineral spirits or turpentine to clean as they easily wash with soap and water.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">水性漆是由颜料、粘合剂和水组成的微小塑料颗粒。它可溶于水，但干燥后会变得耐水。它使用各种类型的粘合剂，如丙烯酸和醇酸树脂。与溶剂型涂料相比，水性涂料的挥发性有机化合物排放量几乎减少了 90%。由于水性涂料环保、无味、颜色选择范围广，因此在家庭应用中很受欢迎。它们不会释放烟雾，也不需要矿物油精或松节油来清洁，因为它们很容易用肥皂和水清洗。</common:generalComment>
